How to configure NTP Client to connect to your NTP server using Ubuntu

Legend: $ Commands to run on command line
	# Comments

Instructions
1. Update/upgrade repository
	$ sudo apt-get update
	$ sudo apt-get upgrade
2. Install ntpdate
	$ sudo apt-get install ntpdate
3. Specify IP and hostname of NTP Server in hosts file
	# added your NTP server's IP and specify a hostname
	$ sudo vim /etc/hosts
4. Verify that the client machine's time is synchronized with NTP Server
	$ sudo ntpdate hostname
	# replace hostname with the hostname you enter in your hosts file
5. Disable systemd timesyncd service on client
	$ sudo timedatectl set-ntp off
6. Install NTP on your client
	$ sudo apt-get install ntp
7. Configure ntp.config file to add NTP Server as the new time server
	$ sudo vim /etc/ntp.conf
	# add "server hostname prefer iburst" to config file where hostname replaced with your actual hostname
8. Restart NTP Server on client
	$ sudo service ntp restart
9. View Time Synchronization Queue
	$ ntpq -ps
